But looking more closely, I notice that some methods call `newString()` helper method which handles null properly, while others call the constructor directly. Looking at the `newStringIso8859_1` method, it calls `new String(bytes, Charsets.ISO_8859_1)` directly without null checking. This would cause a `NullPointerException` when `bytes` is null.

